This is a simple web service that returns a hello greeting
as a JSON object.

It is implemented using starlette.
Project setup is pretty much the same as the standard python
project in 01-remote-idea-python.

Only additional things to note are:
1. Add starlette and uvcorn as packages to be installed
2. The webservice runs by default on port 5100.

Start the webservice this way:
# Source the environment
source venv/bin/acivate

python3 src/application.py 

You can also use the more standard invocation method:

python3 -m uvcorn --host:0.0.0.0 --port=5100 src/application
